# Testing Guidelines

## Stack

`jest` + `supertest` + `ts-jest` — test files co-located with source (`*.test.ts`)

## Test Database

- Use `ttn_stm_test` — never `ttn_stm`. `NODE_ENV=test` routes automatically.
- `afterEach`: `TRUNCATE attachments, comments, tickets, users RESTART IDENTITY CASCADE`
- `afterAll`: `pool.end()`

## Test Types

| Type | What to test | How |
|---|---|---|
| Unit (services) | Happy path, nulls, violations | `jest.mock` on `query` from `src/config/postgres.ts` |
| Integration (controllers) | Status codes, envelope shape, 401/403 | `supertest(app)` + real test DB |
| Middleware | `errorHandler`, `authenticate` | 100% coverage required |
| Job workers | Handler functions directly | Bypass queue; `jsonTransport` for email capture |

## File Location

Co-locate with source:
- `ticket.service.test.ts`
- `ticket.controller.test.ts`
- `auth.middleware.test.ts`

## Assertion Order (always status code first)

```ts
expect(res.status).toBe(200);
expect(res.body.success).toBe(true);
expect(res.body.data).toMatchObject({ title: 'Test' });
```

## Test Data

Use factory functions in `tests/factories.ts` — never inline literals.

## Jest Config (`package.json`)

```json
"jest": {
  "preset": "ts-jest",
  "testEnvironment": "node",
  "setupFilesAfterFramework": ["./jest.setup.ts"],
  "testMatch": ["**/*.test.ts"],
  "collectCoverageFrom": ["src/**/*.ts", "!src/db/**"]
}
```

**Scripts:** `npm test` · `npm run test:watch` · `npm run test:coverage`

## Coverage Targets

| Layer | Minimum |
|---|---|
| Services | 90% |
| Controllers | 80% |
| Middleware / Utils | 100% |
| Job workers | 80% |

## Special Test Scenarios

### Notification Tests
`NODE_ENV=test` activates `jsonTransport`; call worker handlers directly. Assert:
- New-ticket job sends to creator + admin; de-duplicated if same person
- Comment-notification excludes the comment author

### Auto-Close Tests
`AUTO_CLOSE_DELAY_MS=0`; call worker handler directly. Assert all four cases:
- (a) Assignee comment → delayed job scheduled with `jobId = auto-close:{ticketId}`
- (b) Creator reply → job removed from delayed queue
- (c) Deadline fires, no creator reply → `ticket.status === 'CLOSED'`
- (d) Creator replies before job executes → status unchanged

### Attachment Tests
`STORAGE_BACKEND=local`, `STORAGE_LOCAL_DIR=.tmp/test-uploads`; clean up in `afterAll`. Assert:
- Allowed MIME + within size → `201`; `storageKey` absent from response
- Disallowed MIME → `415`; oversize → `400`; over file count → `400`
- Download → `200` with correct `Content-Type` + `Content-Disposition: attachment`
- Caller without ticket access → `403` on list/download
- Delete by non-uploader non-admin → `403`; by uploader → `204`

